===Etymology===
Uncertain: Possibly, {{compound|en|swift|boat}}, or possibly based on an acronym for Shallow Water Inshore Fast Tactical Craft. 

The use as a political term derives from a smear campaign against John Kerry when Texas tycoon Robert J. Perry hired a several Navy swiftboat veterans to form the group ''Swift Boat Veterans for Truth'', which questioned the legitimacy of Kerry's status as a war hero.

